snippet.textDisplay:
I get why people want a PS5 the games are really good but dang is it a bad value for money. Especially the digital edition. The Xbox series X is cheaper than the PS5 digital.. by $20 in the first year and then $120 cheaper every consecutive year.

I hear you go "But its cheaperz! See Xbox X $499 and PS5Di $399!!". You are correct in that statement but the "digital only" part is kinda important since unlike Xbox the PS5's internet access is not free. It will cost you $10 a month just to connect your all digital PS5 to the internet which pans out to about $120 a year just in internet fee's. That means the PS5Di is actually $520 dollars in the first year and $120 just in internet access fee's every year after it.

That is apart from Sony happily touting the need of $70 titles during an economic recession meanwhile all first party Xbox games will be on gamepass.

Also apart from that you can use your old Xbox controllers or third party controllers that are 1/3th or less than the mandatory $70 you have to pony up to Sony if you want any additional controllers.

Pro-tip: Don't buy the PS5. Yes it will suck because you will miss out on a lot of really good exclusive games but its business model is really screwing you over and Sony is not going to listen to any complaints unless it actually affects their bottom line. So see it as an investment so you can get the same quality of games for a more reasonable price in the future.
